{"total_count":23506,"incomplete_results":false,"items":[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390/events","html_url":"https://github.com/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390","id":4507785208,"node_id":"I_kwDOR00Qmc8AAAABDK9X-A","number":390,"title":"test(parity): Semgrep parity tests for the 6 remaining languages (Ruby, PHP, C#, Swift, Kotlin, Rust) + Go AST limitation","user":{"login":"peaktwilight","id":77903714,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc3OTAzNzE0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/77903714?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight","html_url":"https://github.com/peaktwilight","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/peaktwilight/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-23T10:32:34Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T12:14:21Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T12:14:21Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Context\n\nFollows #375. PR https://github.com/0sec-labs/foxguard/pull/391 added per-language Semgrep parity micro-pattern suites for the three biggest production-user languages (JavaScript, Go, Java).\n\nThe remaining 6 languages still have **zero** Semgrep parity tests:\n\n- Ruby\n- PHP\n- C#\n- Swift\n- Kotlin\n- Rust\n\n## Action\n\nMirror `tests/semgrep_parity.rs` (Python) for each. Each new file should:\n\n1. Reuse the same `NormalizedFinding` / `skip_if_semgrep_missing` / `assert_parity` helpers.\n2. Adapt the 6 micro-patterns (`pattern-either`, `metavariable-regex`, `pattern-inside`, `pattern-not-inside`, `pattern-regex`+`pattern-not-regex`, `paths.include/exclude`) to a language-native sink (e.g. Ruby `eval`/`system`, PHP `eval`/`system`, C# `Process.Start`, Swift `system`/`NSExpression`, Kotlin `Runtime.getRuntime().exec`, Rust `Command::new`).\n3. Add a `cargo test --test semgrep_parity_<lang>` step to `.github/workflows/ci.yml` under the `semgrep-parity` job.\n\n## Bonus / blocker — Go AST limitation surfaced by #375\n\nThree of the six Go tests in `tests/semgrep_parity_go.rs` are currently `#[ignore]`d because `tree-sitter-go` rejects Semgrep micro-syntax (`$X`, `...`) at top level — Go requires a `package` clause before any declaration, so the pattern AST parses with an `ERROR` wrapper that foxguard's `first_meaningful_node` cannot drill into. As a result:\n\n- `pattern-inside`, `pattern-not-inside`, `metavariable-regex` all silently degrade for Go.\n- The three ignored tests document the divergence.\n\nFix idea: teach `src/rules/semgrep_compat.rs::first_meaningful_node` to descend into a single `ERROR` child for languages whose grammar rejects bare expressions (Go, Rust, Kotlin), recovering the inner pattern node. Once landed, flip the three Go tests from `#[ignore]` to active and verify parity.\n\n## Severity\n\nMedium — we ship rules in all 9 listed languages but only validate parity in 3 + Python. The Go AST gap is the highest-leverage fix because Go is already #2 by rule count.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0sec-labs/foxguard/issues/390/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321/events","html_url":"https://github.com/golang/go/issues/79321","id":4417966517,"node_id":"I_kwDOAWBuf88AAAABB1TRtQ","number":79321,"title":"cmd/vet: printf analyzer flags conditionally-printf-like functions","user":{"login":"blackpiglet","id":59276555,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU5Mjc2NTU1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/59276555?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet","html_url":"https://github.com/blackpiglet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/blackpiglet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-05-11T03:57:23Z","updated_at":"2026-05-11T14:20:43Z","closed_at":"2026-05-11T13:47:24Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Go version\n\ngo version 1.26.2 linux/amd64\n\n### Output of `go env` in your module/workspace:\n\n```shell\nAR='ar'\nCC='clang'\nCGO_CFLAGS='-O2 -g'\nCGO_CPPFLAGS=''\nCGO_CXXFLAGS='-O2 -g'\nCGO_ENABLED='1'\nCGO_FFLAGS='-O2 -g'\nCGO_LDFLAGS='-O2 -g'\nCXX='clang++'\nGCCGO='gccgo'\nGO111MODULE='on'\nGOARCH='arm64'\nGOARM64='v8.0'\nGOAUTH='netrc'\nGOBIN='/Users/jxun/go/bin/'\nGOCACHE='/Users/jxun/Library/Caches/go-build'\nGOCACHEPROG=''\nGODEBUG=''\nGOENV='/Users/jxun/Library/Application Support/go/env'\nGOEXE=''\nGOEXPERIMENT=''\nGOFIPS140='off'\nGOFLAGS=''\nGOGCCFLAGS='-fPIC -arch arm64 -pthread -fno-caret-diagnostics -Qunused-arguments -fmessage-length=0 -ffile-prefix-map=/var/folders/hq/769fg_2s04q22kldsd7g5lmw0000gp/T/go-build2399194625=/tmp/go-build -gno-record-gcc-switches -fno-common'\nGOHOSTARCH='arm64'\nGOHOSTOS='darwin'\nGOINSECURE=''\nGOMOD='/dev/null'\nGOMODCACHE='/Users/jxun/go/pkg/mod'\nGONOPROXY=''\nGONOSUMDB=''\nGOOS='darwin'\nGOPATH='/Users/jxun/go'\nGOPRIVATE=''\nGOPROXY='https://goproxy.cn'\nGOROOT='/usr/local/go'\nGOSUMDB='sum.golang.org'\nGOTELEMETRY='local'\nGOTELEMETRYDIR='/Users/jxun/Library/Application Support/go/telemetry'\nGOTMPDIR=''\nGOTOOLCHAIN='auto'\nGOTOOLDIR='/usr/local/go/pkg/tool/darwin_arm64'\nGOVCS=''\nGOVERSION='go1.26.3'\nGOWORK=''\nPKG_CONFIG='pkg-config'\n```\n\n### What did you do?\n\nI ran some GitHub golangci-lint actions for `[velero](https://github.com/velero-io/velero.git)` repository.\n\nThe `golangci-lint` version is `v2.12.0`.\n\n`go vet` reported some false positive lint errors.\nThis is the failed GitHub linter action: https://github.com/velero-io/velero/actions/runs/25544430787/job/74977276083\n\n### What did you see happen?\n\nSome `printf` govet errors are reported.\n\n``` bash\n  Error: pkg/datamover/backup_micro_service.go:253:77: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \t\tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.dataUpload, false, datapath.EventReasonCompleted, string(backupBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t                                                                          ^\n  Error: pkg/datamover/backup_micro_service.go:293:75: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.dataUpload, false, datapath.EventReasonProgress, string(progressBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t                                                                         ^\n  Error: pkg/datamover/restore_micro_service.go:231:79: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \t\tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.dataDownload, false, datapath.EventReasonCompleted, string(restoreBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t                                                                            ^\n  Error: pkg/datamover/restore_micro_service.go:271:77: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.dataDownload, false, datapath.EventReasonProgress, string(progressBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t                                                                           ^\n  Error: pkg/podvolume/backup_micro_service.go:250:70: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \t\tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.pvb, false, datapath.EventReasonCompleted, string(backupBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t                                                                   ^\n  Error: pkg/podvolume/backup_micro_service.go:290:68: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.pvb, false, datapath.EventReasonProgress, string(progressBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t                                                                  ^\n  Error: pkg/podvolume/restore_micro_service.go:240:70: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \t\tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.pvr, false, datapath.EventReasonCompleted, string(restoreBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t                                                                   ^\n  Error: pkg/podvolume/restore_micro_service.go:251:66: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.pvr, false, datapath.EventReasonFailed, evtMsg) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t                                                                ^\n  Error: pkg/podvolume/restore_micro_service.go:285:68: printf: non-constant format string in call to (github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.EventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \tr.eventRecorder.Event(r.pvr, false, datapath.EventReasonProgress, string(progressBytes)) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t                                                                  ^\n  Error: pkg/util/kube/event.go:126:42: printf: non-constant format string in call to (*github.com/vmware-tanzu/velero/pkg/util/kube.eventRecorder).Event (govet)\n  \t\ter.Event(object, false, sentinelEvent, sentinelEvent) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t                                       ^\n  Error: pkg/util/kube/event_test.go:184:64: directive `//nolint:govet false positive for govet` should match `//nolint[:<comma-separated-linters>] [// <explanation>]` (nolintlint)\n  \t\t\t\t\trecorder.EndingEvent(pod, e.warning, e.reason, e.message) //nolint:govet false positive for govet\n  \t\t\t\t\t                                                          ^\n  Error: pkg/util/kube/event_test.go:186:58: directive `//nolint:govet false positive for govet` should match `//nolint[:<comma-separated-linters>] [// <explanation>]` (nolintlint)\n\n``` \n\n### What did you expect to see?\n\nThere should be no linter error reported.\n\nThis is the analysis of the Velero code to prove the linter error is a false positive.\nThis is one of the locations reporting the error. The linter reported that the k8s.io/client-go/tools/record/event.go's `Eventf` function eventually calls the `fmt.Sprintf`. As a result, the linter reports an error because there is no format string passed in.\n\nhttps://github.com/velero-io/velero/blob/038d78057668bb010a9cc1552982d4321b3c7ce5/pkg/util/kube/event.go#L125-L129\n``` go\n\tif sentinelEvent != \"\" {\n\t\ter.Event(object, false, sentinelEvent, sentinelEvent)\n\t} else {\n\t\ter.log.Warn(\"More than one ending events, ignore\")\n\t}\n```\n\nHowever, Velero calls different Event functions on different conditions. If there is no additional format string, Velero will call `er.recorder.Event` instead of `er.recorder.Eventf`.\nAs a result, this is not an printf linter issue.\nhttps://github.com/velero-io/velero/blob/038d78057668bb010a9cc1552982d4321b3c7ce5/pkg/util/kube/event.go#L87-L102\n``` go\nfunc (er *eventRecorder) Event(object runtime.Object, warning bool, reason string, message string, a ...any) {\n\tif er.broadcaster == nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\teventType := corev1api.EventTypeNormal\n\tif warning {\n\t\teventType = corev1api.EventTypeWarning\n\t}\n\n\tif len(a) > 0 {\n\t\ter.recorder.Eventf(object, eventType, reason, message, a...)\n\t} else {\n\t\ter.recorder.Event(object, eventType, reason, message)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/golang/go/issues/79321/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"duplicate","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2893","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2893/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2893/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2893/events","html_url":"https://github.com/micro/go-micro/issues/2893","id":4260076172,"node_id":"I_kwDOAb3RHs7965qM","number":2893,"title":"[FEATURE] Reintroduce Prometheus monitoring wrapper for go-micro","user":{"login":"BombartSimon","id":97341273,"node_id":"U_kgDOBc1PWQ","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/97341273?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon","html_url":"https://github.com/BombartSimon","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BombartSimon/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":165972695,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxNjU5NzI2OTU=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"84b6eb","default":true,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-04-14T06:59:43Z","updated_at":"2026-04-15T08:24:45Z","closed_at":"2026-04-15T08:24:45Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\nThe Prometheus monitoring wrapper previously available in the plugins repository (`wrapper/monitoring/prometheus`) is no longer easily usable or maintained with recent versions of go-micro.\n\nAs a result, integrating Prometheus metrics into go-micro services now requires custom implementations, which leads to:\n\n* duplicated effort across projects\n* inconsistent metrics exposure\n* increased maintenance overhead\n\n## Describe the solution you'd like\n\nReintroduce and officially support a Prometheus monitoring wrapper for go-micro (v5), similar to the one previously available here:\n[https://github.com/go-micro/plugins/tree/main/v5/wrapper/monitoring/prometheus](https://github.com/go-micro/plugins/tree/main/v5/wrapper/monitoring/prometheus)\n\nThe wrapper should:\n\n* expose standard metrics (request count, latency, errors)\n* integrate seamlessly with go-micro handlers and clients\n* follow current go-micro v5 patterns and interfaces\n* be production-ready and documented\n\n## Describe alternatives you've considered\n\n* Implementing a custom middleware per service → not reusable and error-prone\n* Using external HTTP middleware → does not integrate well with go-micro RPC flow\n* Manual instrumentation → verbose and inconsistent across services\n\n## Use case\n\nIn a microservices architecture using go-micro, having a standardized Prometheus wrapper allows consistent observability across all services without rewriting instrumentation logic.\n\n**Example:**\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/micro/go-micro/v5\"\n    prom \"github.com/go-micro/plugins/v5/wrapper/monitoring/prometheus\"\n)\n\nservice := micro.NewService(\n    micro.Name(\"example.service\"),\n    micro.WrapHandler(prom.NewHandlerWrapper()),\n    micro.WrapClient(prom.NewClientWrapper()),\n)\n\nservice.Init()\n\nif err := service.Run(); err != nil {\n    panic(err)\n}\n```\n\n## Implementation ideas (optional)\n\n* Update the existing Prometheus wrapper to be compatible with go-micro v5\n* Ensure compatibility with the current plugin system\n* Add configurable metrics (namespace, labels, buckets, etc.)\n* Provide an example service + Prometheus scrape config\n* Possibly align with OpenTelemetry if relevant\n\n## Additional context\n\nPrometheus is widely adopted for monitoring microservices, and having a first-class wrapper in go-micro would greatly improve developer experience and standardization.\n\nThe previous implementation could serve as a solid base but may require refactoring to align with the latest go-micro APIs.\n\n## Checklist\n\n* [ ] I've searched existing issues and this is not a duplicate\n* [ ] I've checked the roadmap and this isn't already planned\n* [x] I've provided a clear use case\n* [x] I'd be willing to submit a PR for this feature (optional)\n\n## Helpful Resources\n\n* [Roadmap](https://github.com/micro/go-micro/blob/master/ROADMAP.md)\n* [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/micro/go-micro/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md)\n* [Architecture Docs](https://github.com/micro/go-micro/tree/master/internal/website/docs/architecture.md)\n* [Discord 