ll,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### 📝 Description\nA recent layout refactor aimed at optimizing mini-games for mobile viewports has unintentionally locked the game modals into a rigid, narrow, vertical layout. This has introduced dual layout bugs:\n**On Desktops:** The modals are forced into a narrow phone-like column, creating massive empty margins and squishing interactive UI components (like charts, boards, and text).\n\n**On Mobile:** Because the narrow container layout scales down rigidly or overflows with detailed components (e.g., charts, grids, reference tables), the game interface scales down to a micro-sized, unreadable column in the center of the screen.\n\n### 🔄 Steps to Reproduce\n1. Go to app\n2. Click on any game(Coin Flip,Collatz Conjecture, Morse Code Translator, or Armstrong Number Checker)\n3. Observe the narrow, squished layout on a standard desktop screen resolution.\n4. Toggle device toolbar simulation to a mobile screen width (e.g., 400px wide) or open the site on an actual smartphone device.\n5. Observe the micro-scaled, unreadable UI components that are too narrow for standard interaction.\n<img width=\"1024\" height=\"522\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1f6ef161-7f3f-4da0-8747-125ed4bdecd8\" />\n\n<img width=\"1023\" height=\"515\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f3f13556-a23f-423c-afa3-3d802ebcb7e4\" />\n\n<img width=\"1049\" height=\"888\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/213a508c-9b04-4e57-93ec-da8c2408b20c\" />\n\n<img width=\"720\" height=\"1600\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4938e87c-7fa2-4992-ba05-69f89c7a7550\" />\n\n<img width=\"460\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/95d7864f-276f-452a-8043-2a8194f021a7\" />\n\n### 🎯 Expected Behavior\n**On Desktop:** Modals should expand comfortably horizontally (e.g., max-width: 800px or a fluid percentage), allowing charts, grids, and text to layout side-by-side or expand naturally.\n**On Mobile:** The layout container should expand fluidly to fill roughly 90%–95% of the mobile viewport width, ensuring text remains legible and buttons are easily tappable without forcing the entire card to shrink down rigidly.\n### ❌ Actual Behavior / Error Logs\n### 💻 Environment\n- **OS:** Windows 11\n- **Browser:** Chrome\n\n---\n- [x] I am a registered **GSSoC 2026** contributor.\n- [x] I want to be assigned to fix this issue.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/steam-bell-92/python-mini-project/issues/631/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/steam-bell-92/python-mini-project/issues/631/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS/issues/3650","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS/issues/3650/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS/issues/3650/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS/issues/3650/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS/issues/3650","id":4490785791,"node_id":"I_kwDOCQEPd88AAAABC6vz_w","number":3650,"title":"RM Boxer w. TBS Micro TX random RX Loss on V4.0.0","user":{"login":"prodrone7","id":286504166,"node_id":"U_kgDOERO05g","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/286504166?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/prodrone7","html_url":"https://github.com/prodrone7","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/prodrone