.com/users/kndtran/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kndtran/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":6140422687,"node_id":"LA_kwDOJH_K4M8AAAABbf9qHw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ggml-org/llama.cpp/labels/bug-unconfirmed","name":"bug-unconfirmed","color":"FEF2C0","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-04-13T17:26:18Z","updated_at":"2026-05-12T05:17:06Z","closed_at":"2026-05-12T05:17:06Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Name and Version\n\nversion: b8779 (75f3bc94e)\n\n### Operating systems\n\n_No response_\n\n### Which llama.cpp modules do you know to be affected?\n\nPython/Bash scripts\n\n### Command line\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Problem description & steps to reproduce\n\ncc @gabe-l-hart  \n\nConverting a LoRA adapter for a GraniteMoe model (e.g. `granite-4.0-micro`) fails because `LoraTorchTensor` does not implement `split()`.\n\n`GraniteMoeModel.modify_tensors` calls `data_torch.split(ffn_dim, dim=-2)` to separate merged gate/up FFN weights (`input_linear.weight`, `shared_mlp.input_linear.weight`). During LoRA conversion these tensors are `LoraTorchTensor` objects, which implement `reshape`, `permute`, `transpose`, `__getitem__`, etc. but not `split()`. This likely affects any MoE architecture that merges gate/up projections into a single tensor.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n```bash\n# Clone the repo (contains GraniteMoe LoRA adapters)\nhf download ibm-granite/granite-lib-rag-r1.0 --local-dir ./granite-lib-rag-r1.0\ncd granite-lib-rag-r1.0\n\n# Clone llama.cpp\ngit clone --single-branch --branch master https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp.git _ollama/llama.cpp\n\n# Create venv and install dependencies\npython3 -m venv .venv\nsource .venv/bin/activate\npip install --upgrade pip\npip install huggingface_hub\npip install -r _ollama/llama.cpp/requirements/requirements-convert_lora_to_gguf.txt\n\n# Download base model weights\nhf download ibm-granite/granite-4.0-micro --local-dir _ollama/models/granite-4.0-micro\n\n# Convert query_clarification LoRA — this triggers the error\npython _ollama/llama.cpp/convert_lora_to_gguf.py \\\n  query_clarification/granite-4.0-micro/lora \\\n  --base _ollama/models/granite-4.0-micro \\\n  --outtype f16\n```\n\n\n### First Bad Commit\n\n_No response_\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n<details>\n<summary>Logs</summary>\n<!-- Copy-pasted short logs go into the \"console\" area here -->\n\n```console\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"convert_lora_to_gguf.py\", line 502, in <module>\n    model_instance.write()\n  File \"convert_hf_to_gguf.py\", line 934, in write\n    self.prepare_tensors()\n  File \"convert_hf_to_gguf.py\", line 2983, in prepare_tensors\n    super().prepare_tensors()\n  File \"convert_hf_to_gguf.py\", line 794, in prepare_tensors\n    for new_name, data_torch in (self.modify_tensors(data_torch, name, bid)):\n  File \"convert_lora_to_gguf.py\", line 459, in modify_tensors\n    dest = list(super().modify_tensors(data_torch, name, bid))\n  File \"convert_hf_to_gguf.py\", line 10748, in modify_tensors\n    yield from GraniteMoeModel.modify_tensors(self, data_torch, name, bid)\n  File \"convert_hf_to_gguf.py\", line 10648, in modify_tensors\n    gate, up = data_torch.split(ffn_dim, dim=-2)\nAttributeError: 'LoraTorchTensor' object has no attribute 'split'\n```\n</details>\n\n<!-- Long logs that you upload as files go here, outside the \"console\" area -->\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ggml-org/llama.cpp/issues/21864/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"