api.github.com/users/Copilot/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Describe the bug\nThe backgound is that we need to enable etcd server auth due to some security concerns.\n\nEtcd server has a special authentication design which causes a serious performance problem of */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* API.\n\nFrom our observation, a normal 3-nodes etcd cluster whose spec like 64C 256G HDD can only support less than around 100 QPS for authentication requests.\n\nIn current default go-micro registry plugin setting and gRPC server setting, gRPC server will do a registry by using **KeepAliveOnce** every RegisterInterval(default 30s). **KeepAliveOnce** will use */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* once to establish the stream.\n\nIn our Prod env, we have a k8s cluster which contains over 4000 service pods results in a steady */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* QPS around 110.\n\nWhen we start to enable the etcd auth, the etcd cluster can not handle such */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* QPS causes the business **KeepAliveOnce** failed and deregister from etcd server after registryTTL.\n\nThe upstream **Watch** the change and **Delete** downstream server nodes from registry cache which result in an empty cache finally. \n\nWhen the cache has been cleared, causes another cache penetration problem which is that a gRPC call will call etcd to get downstream nodes from etcd when cache is empty or invalid, but etcd server does not have the info in this time because downstream can not keep the registry hearbeat due to the */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* problem.\n\nThe result is that all gRPC request penetrate to etcd and failed at last.\n\nWe wanna handle these two problems:\n- 1. Limit the request to etcd when cache is empty to avoid the penetration issue.\n- 2. Use \"KeepAlive\" instead of \"KeepAliveOnce\" to address */etcdserverpb.Auth/Authenticate* QPS issue.\n\n\n## To Reproduce\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. create a 4000+ service pods which use default go-micro registry settings.\n2. preconfigure the etcd username and passwd.\n3. enable etcd cluster auth.\n## Environment\n- Go Micro version: \n  - github.com/go-micro/plugins/v4/client/grpc v1.2.1\n  - github.com/go-micro/plugins/v4/registry/etcd v1.2.0\n  - github.com/go-micro/plugins/v4/server/grpc v1.2.0\n  - go-micro.dev/v4 v4.9.0\n  - go.etcd.io/etcd/client/v3 v3.5.2\n- Go version: 1.18\n- OS: Ubuntu 20.04\n- Plugins used: \n  - etcd registry\n\n## Logs\nserver side monitor\n\n<img width=\"1453\" height=\"657\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dffe2a93-df86-47e5-8116-d8c6446337bf\" />\n\n## Resources\n- [Documentation](https://github.com/micro/go-micro/tree/master/internal/website/docs)\n- [Examples](https://github.com/micro/go-micro/tree/master/internal/website/docs/examples)\n- [API Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/go-micro.dev/v5)\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2821/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/micro/go-micro/issues/2821/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ventd/ventd/issues/1119","id":4459332014,"node_id":"I_kwDOSB_Gbs8AAAABCcwBrg","number":1119,"title":"wizard: propose msi-ec DKMS install for MSI laptops with msi_wmi_platform + no PWM","user":{"login":"PhoenixDnB","id":101230040,"node_id":"U_kgDOBgil2A","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/101230040?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB","html_url":"https://github.com/PhoenixDnB","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/PhoenixDnB/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10686945122,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSB_Gbs8AAAACfP3XYg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/labels/bug","name":"bug","color":"d73a4a","default":true,"description":"Something isn't working"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-16T08:55:11Z","updated_at":"2026-05-16T09:01:10Z","closed_at":"2026-05-16T09:01:10Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\n#1116 surfaced a class of host where ventd reaches the wizard's \"no fan controllers found\" terminal state silently, even though an actively-maintained DKMS module ([BeardOverflow/msi-ec](https://github.com/BeardOverflow/msi-ec)) would unblock fan control. PR #1104 stopped ventd misrouting these hosts to IT8688E; this issue is the follow-up to actually give them a path forward.\n\n## Concrete case (from #1116)\n\n- DMI: `Micro-Star International Co., Ltd.` / `MS-16R8` (Thin GF63 12U series)\n- Chassis: Notebook (DMI type 10)\n- Hwmon loaded: `msi_wmi_platform` — tach-only, 4 `fan*_input` slots, no `pwm*`\n- Outcome on v0.7.0: `identifyDriverNeeds` returns `[]` (correct, post-#1104), `setup.go::discoverHwmonControls` finds no controllable channels (correct), `emitDMICandidates` emits `IDDMINoMatch` (\"your board isn't in the known-hardware list\"). User has no actionable path inside ventd.\n\nThe msi-ec module supports MS-16R8 across several EC firmware revisions (`16R8IMS1.107` / `.108` / `.111` / `.117`). Once loaded it exposes `pwm1` + `fan1_input` via standard hwmon and ventd's normal flow picks it up — but ventd doesn't offer to install it.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nExtend `internal/hwmon/autoload.go::knownDriverNeeds` (or a new laptop-specific seed table) with a `msi_ec` `DriverNeed`:\n\n  - `Module: msi-ec`\n  - `RepoURL: https://github.com/BeardOverflow/msi-ec`\n  - `Branch: main`\n  - DMITriggers: `BoardVendorContains: micro-star`/`msi` **AND** chassis is Notebook (DMI `chassis_type` ∈ `{Portable, Laptop, Notebook, Sub Notebook, Convertible}` — same predicate as `RULE-GPU-PR2D-06`'s `nvml.LaptopDGPU`) **AND** `msi_wmi_platform` in hwmon set.\n\nThe existing install pipeline (PR-D + cleanup + preflight chain) covers the rest unchanged: build, sign, DKMS-register, modprobe, verify \"PWM channels appeared\" via `install_steps.stepVerify`.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- msi-ec supports a closed-set list of EC firmware revisions; on unsupported revisions modprobe binds but exposes no `pwm1`. `stepVerify` already handles \"module loaded but no PWM appeared\" via `ErrNoPWMChannelsAppeared`; the wizard's retry-loop already advances to the next `DriverNeed` candidate on that error class (`setup.go:954`). With `msi-ec` as the only candidate, the failure-mode is monitor-only with a clean, actionable diag entry (\"your EC firmware revision isn't yet supported by msi-ec; file an issue with your EC dump\") — distinct from today's silent dead-end.\n- Add a parallel doctor card pointing to BeardOverflow's \"report your model\" issue template — same pattern as the existing nbfc-linux contribution invite.\n- License: msi-ec is GPL-2.0. The DKMS install pipeline is identical to the existing it87 / nct6687d cases.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- A host that matches the new trigger runs `ventd --probe-modules` (or the web-UI wizard) and lands on `msi-ec` as the proposed install.\n- A board outside msi-ec's supported list still produces the honest \"no fan controllers\" outcome but with a doctor card linking BeardOverflow/msi-ec/issues + a one-line dmidecode snippet for the operator to paste into the report.\n- HudsonPH or another GF63 12U operator can confirm the wizard flow end-to-end.\n\n## Why this matters\n\nWithout this, every MSI laptop user with a non-mainline-supported model hits the same terminal \"no fan controllers\" surface even after #1104. The wizard's predict-not-react design exists exactly so the next user doesn't have to know about BeardOverflow/msi-ec before they can use ventd.\n\nRefs #1116","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ventd/ventd/issues/1119/timeline","performed_via_github